hr.caellian.flow.conversion

Interface Converter<T,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - input type.
    R - output type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<T,R>

    public interface Converter<T,R>
extends java.util.function.Function<T,R>
    Converter is a function with input and output IDs. IDs are essential to allow conversion manager to differentiate between conversion functions.

    Using ID instead of using object types is beneficial as it allows users to use a same class for different Flux types and still work with conversion management system. Object type comparison is not flexible enough to support generics in Java.

    Since:
    1.0.0
